- **Evidence:** [main.py:L145-L192](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/main.py#L145-L192)
- **Proof:** [_run_bootstrap_sequence](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/main.py#148-200) handles `genesis` mode by generating a 32-byte root key ([L153](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/main.py#L153)), registering the `kernel_root` identity ([L166-L172](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/main.py#L166-L172)), and atomically switching to `normal` mode via config rewrite ([L175-L182](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/main.py#L175-L182)).

