## ⚡ PHASE 2: EVENT BUS (NERVOUS SYSTEM)

### 1. Deterministic Sequential Router
- **Evidence:** [bus.py:L259-L289](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/event_bus/bus.py#L259-L289).
- **Proof:** [_dispatch](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/event_bus/bus.py#258-289) executes subscribers in a blocking, single-threaded loop ([L261](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/event_bus/bus.py#L261)). Subscribers are pre-sorted by UUID during registration ([L221](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/event_bus/bus.py#L221)) to guarantee order.

### 2. Backpressure Controller (Hysteresis)
- **Evidence:** [bus.py:L173-L185](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/event_bus/bus.py#L173-L185) and `BackpressureController` implementation (not shown but verified).
- **Proof:** [publish](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/event_bus/bus.py#149-208) checks the real queue depth against the controller before accepting new events ([L175](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/event_bus/bus.py#L175)), raising `POLICY_BUDGET_EXCEEDED` on violation.

### 3. Idempotent Replay Engine
- **Evidence:** [bus.py:L223-L250](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/event_bus/bus.py#L223-L250).
- **Proof:** [replay_events](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/event_bus/bus.py#223-250) fetches historical events by range ([L230](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/event_bus/bus.py#L230)) and re-dispatches them with an explicit `replay_context` ([L232-L237](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/event_bus/bus.py#L232-L237)) to ensure no new primary state is created.

### 4. Dead-Letter Queue (DLQ)
- **Evidence:** [bus.py:L275-L279](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/event_bus/bus.py#L275-L279).
- **Proof:** All subscriber exceptions are caught and routed to the DLQ with the original event and failure metadata preserved ([L275](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/event_bus/bus.py#L275)).

